article_title: Next Enrollment Season for Affordable Care Act Kicks Off
article_text:
The third open enrollment season under the Affordable Care Act kicked off with subdued consumer activity and scant signs of major technology problems that could tamp down sign ups.

The Obama administration was expecting a slow sign-up pace Sunday because of the weekend timing but is gearing up for brisker enrollment in the weeks to come. Open enrollment for new and returning customers on the federal marketplace HealthCare.gov and...
